      "content": "I hear how heavy and isolating these feelings are, especially when trying to navigate a \"new normal\" after such a profound loss seems impossible. Please remember that even gray days or functioning like a ghost don't mean you aren't real, but your pain is valid regardless of how invisible it feels to others. While deep grief can make trust difficult, professional therapists are trained to hold complex spaces where your pain is the only thing that matters.",
